                                    <watches>1</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12614338" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Thu, 17 Jul 2008 14:55:09 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Check out &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-561&quot; title=&quot;Solr replication by Solr (for windows also)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-561&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-561&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, it adds a pointer from the SolrCore to it&apos;s CoreDescriptor, uses a CoreDescriptor even for a single core (+ the ability to reload it), and the CoreDescriptor now has a pointer to it&apos;s MultiCore instance.  We could add a getter to that.... so it would be something like core.getCoreDescriptor().getMulticore()&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12614340" author="ryantxu" created="Thu, 17 Jul 2008 15:01:31 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I like that idea.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12614645" author="noble.paul" created="Fri, 18 Jul 2008 05:41:56 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I have extracted the relevant portions of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-561&quot; title=&quot;Solr replication by Solr (for windows also)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-561&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-561&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; and created this patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12614744" author="ryantxu" created="Fri, 18 Jul 2008 16:05:40 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m changing the issue name/description so it represents what the patch does&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12614757" author="ryantxu" created="Fri, 18 Jul 2008 16:25:07 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good &amp;#8211; I made two small changes:&lt;br/&gt;
1. MultiCore is now final in CoreDescriptor&lt;br/&gt;
2. Made sure we had the 1.2 SolrCore constructor with only two params and removed the other constructor options that have been added since 1.2&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;i&apos;ll commit this in a sec&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12614763" author="yseeley@gmail.com" created="Fri, 18 Jul 2008 16:55:59 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt; A couple of items I noticed about this patch:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;the old core is now immediately closed instead of being finalized... this can cause exceptions for requests that are currently in flight, right?&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;CoreDescriptor can now have it&apos;s core changed (via reloadCore).  Doesn&apos;t that now open up thread safety issues?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

</comment>
                            <comment id="12614767" author="ryantxu" created="Fri, 18 Jul 2008 17:08:11 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;You talking about the reloadCore() method on CoreDescriptor?&lt;br/&gt;
I think we should remove that and only use: multicore.reload(CoreDescriptor dcore)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;What is the finalize issue?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12614830" author="noble.paul" created="Fri, 18 Jul 2008 19:04:03 +0100"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;CoreDescriptor can now have it&apos;s core changed (via reloadCore). Doesn&apos;t that now open up thread safety issues?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;yes. remove the &lt;em&gt;reloadCore()&lt;/em&gt; method from &lt;em&gt;CoreDescriptor&lt;/em&gt; for the time being. When we put it let us think more about it. 1.3 does not need it. &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-561&quot; title=&quot;Solr replication by Solr (for windows also)&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-561&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-561&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; needs it. &lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
